{
  "video_id": "fD_ho_ofY6A",
  "title": "Unity 5 Graphics - The Standard Shader - Unity Official Tutorials",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3150.0,
      "end_time": 7520.0,
      "text": "The Standard Shader is a powerful and versatile shader."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 7520.0,
      "end_time": 9520.0,
      "text": "This single physically-based shader"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9520.0,
      "end_time": 11520.0,
      "text": "can be used to make such a wide variety"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11520.0,
      "end_time": 13520.0,
      "text": "of materials it&#39;s easily"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13520.0,
      "end_time": 15520.0,
      "text": "possible that this one shader can make"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15520.0,
      "end_time": 19812.0,
      "text": "every material in a given project."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 19812.0,
      "end_time": 24026.0,
      "text": "The standard is used to create Unity&#39;s default material."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24026.0,
      "end_time": 26026.0,
      "text": "So all mesh rendered using"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26026.0,
      "end_time": 33412.0,
      "text": "the default material will be using the standard shader."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 33412.0,
      "end_time": 36930.0,
      "text": "All new materials that are created"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 36930.0,
      "end_time": 40121.0,
      "text": "will use the standard shader as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 40121.0,
      "end_time": 42611.0,
      "text": "To change the shader used by a material"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 42611.0,
      "end_time": 46046.0,
      "text": "select the Shader menu on the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 46046.0,
      "end_time": 49971.0,
      "text": "Select Standard to use the standard shader."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 49971.0,
      "end_time": 51971.0,
      "text": "It is worth noting the Unity"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 51971.0,
      "end_time": 53971.0,
      "text": "has shaders available for both"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53971.0,
      "end_time": 57736.0,
      "text": "popular approaches to physically-based rendering."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 57736.0,
      "end_time": 59930.0,
      "text": "Metallic, as default,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59930.0,
      "end_time": 61613.0,
      "text": "and specular."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61613.0,
      "end_time": 63251.0,
      "text": "To choose the standard shader"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63251.0,
      "end_time": 65167.0,
      "text": "using the specular approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65167.0,
      "end_time": 68475.0,
      "text": "select Standard (Specular Setup)."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68475.0,
      "end_time": 70475.0,
      "text": "Otherwise use Standard"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 70475.0,
      "end_time": 74750.0,
      "text": "for the metallic approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74750.0,
      "end_time": 76750.0,
      "text": "It is important to understand that the"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 76750.0,
      "end_time": 79337.0,
      "text": "metallic approach to physically-based shading"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 79337.0,
      "end_time": 81337.0,
      "text": "is not only for materials which are"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81337.0,
      "end_time": 83696.0,
      "text": "supposed to look metallic."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 83696.0,
      "end_time": 85696.0,
      "text": "This mode is known as metallic"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 85696.0,
      "end_time": 87696.0,
      "text": "because this approach is based on"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 87696.0,
      "end_time": 90761.0,
      "text": "defining how metallic or non-metallic"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 90761.0,
      "end_time": 93427.0,
      "text": "that material&#39;s surface is."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 93427.0,
      "end_time": 95703.0,
      "text": "This is opposed to the specular approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 95703.0,
      "end_time": 97451.0,
      "text": "which defines how specular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 97451.0,
      "end_time": 100505.0,
      "text": "or non-specular that surface is."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 100505.0,
      "end_time": 102505.0,
      "text": "Both approaches are valid ways to"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 102505.0,
      "end_time": 107459.0,
      "text": "describe a physically-based material."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 107459.0,
      "end_time": 109459.0,
      "text": "This physically-based material is"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 109459.0,
      "end_time": 111695.0,
      "text": "still a standard Unity material"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 111695.0,
      "end_time": 113695.0,
      "text": "and this material is associated"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 113695.0,
      "end_time": 120014.0,
      "text": "with a renderer in the same way as usual."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 120014.0,
      "end_time": 123601.0,
      "text": "There are three sections to the standard shader."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 123601.0,
      "end_time": 125601.0,
      "text": "Rendering Mode."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 125601.0,
      "end_time": 127601.0,
      "text": "Main Maps"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 127601.0,
      "end_time": 131865.0,
      "text": "and Secondary Maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131865.0,
      "end_time": 134685.0,
      "text": "The standard shader has four rendering modes."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 134685.0,
      "end_time": 139038.0,
      "text": "Opaque, Cutout, Fade and Transparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 139038.0,
      "end_time": 143167.0,
      "text": "Most materials are opaque, or solid materials."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143167.0,
      "end_time": 146350.0,
      "text": "Opaque is the default render mode."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 146350.0,
      "end_time": 149225.0,
      "text": "For transparent materials, such as glass,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 149225.0,
      "end_time": 151656.0,
      "text": "choose Transparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 151656.0,
      "end_time": 154142.0,
      "text": "In transparent rendering mode"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 154142.0,
      "end_time": 156819.0,
      "text": "the alpha channel on the diffuse colour property"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 156819.0,
      "end_time": 161569.0,
      "text": "is used to control the level of transparency."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 161569.0,
      "end_time": 163918.0,
      "text": "With rendering mode cutout"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 163918.0,
      "end_time": 165918.0,
      "text": "the alpha channel of the diffuse image"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 165918.0,
      "end_time": 169689.0,
      "text": "is used to mask out parts of the texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 169689.0,
      "end_time": 173240.0,
      "text": "If the alpha channel has a gradient value to the mask"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 173240.0,
      "end_time": 175240.0,
      "text": "the alpha cutoff slider can be used"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 175240.0,
      "end_time": 177240.0,
      "text": "to adjust the shape of the cutout."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 177240.0,
      "end_time": 182546.0,
      "text": "based on the strength of the mask in the alpha channel."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 182546.0,
      "end_time": 184546.0,
      "text": "Rendering mode fade is similar"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 184546.0,
      "end_time": 187509.0,
      "text": "to rendering mode transparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 187509.0,
      "end_time": 189509.0,
      "text": "Fade is intended for fading out"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 189509.0,
      "end_time": 192192.0,
      "text": "game objects on screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 192192.0,
      "end_time": 194192.0,
      "text": "With rendering mode transparent"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 194192.0,
      "end_time": 196750.0,
      "text": "a transparent material will preserve it&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 196750.0,
      "end_time": 200681.0,
      "text": "reflectivity regardless of it&#39;s alpha value."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 200681.0,
      "end_time": 202681.0,
      "text": "Fade however will fade all"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 202681.0,
      "end_time": 204681.0,
      "text": "relevant aspects of the material"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 204681.0,
      "end_time": 210347.0,
      "text": "so the faded material is completely invisible."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 210347.0,
      "end_time": 214361.0,
      "text": "The main map section defines the look of the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 214361.0,
      "end_time": 217301.0,
      "text": "Before going in to the details of each property"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 217301.0,
      "end_time": 221314.0,
      "text": "there are a few subjects that are worth covering first."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 221314.0,
      "end_time": 223131.0,
      "text": "Optimisation."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 223131.0,
      "end_time": 226613.0,
      "text": "The standard shader is highly optimised."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 226613.0,
      "end_time": 228613.0,
      "text": "When the standard shader is built"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 228613.0,
      "end_time": 231113.0,
      "text": "two important things happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 231113.0,
      "end_time": 235240.0,
      "text": "All properties that are not being used are discarded."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 235240.0,
      "end_time": 237240.0,
      "text": "The build target is checked"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 237240.0,
      "end_time": 240559.0,
      "text": "and the shader is optimised for that device."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 240559.0,
      "end_time": 243653.0,
      "text": "Because of this there is no need to populate every"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 243653.0,
      "end_time": 247681.0,
      "text": "property with a map or values."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 247681.0,
      "end_time": 249681.0,
      "text": "And there is no need to worry about wasted"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 249681.0,
      "end_time": 255750.0,
      "text": "resources due to unused properties."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 255750.0,
      "end_time": 258451.0,
      "text": "Physically-based shading."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 258451.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260451.00000000003,
      "text": "Physically-based shading tries to define"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 260451.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263952.0,
      "text": "certain physical aspects of a material&#39;s surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 263952.0,
      "end_time": 265952.0,
      "text": "Including it&#39;s diffuse colour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 265952.0,
      "end_time": 267952.0,
      "text": "specular refection and other properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 267952.0,
      "end_time": 270355.0,
      "text": "so the material behaves correctly"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 270355.0,
      "end_time": 273938.0,
      "text": "and believably in all lighting environments."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 273938.0,
      "end_time": 276325.0,
      "text": "The response of the scene lighting to the material"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 276325.0,
      "end_time": 278325.0,
      "text": "created with a physically based shader"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 278325.0,
      "end_time": 281839.0,
      "text": "mimics light in the real physical world."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 281839.0,
      "end_time": 283839.0,
      "text": "This means that even though there is"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 283839.0,
      "end_time": 285839.0,
      "text": "full control over the values on"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 285839.0,
      "end_time": 288613.0,
      "text": "all of the properties in the standard shader"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 288613.0,
      "end_time": 290613.0,
      "text": "there are certain ranges of values that"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 290613.0,
      "end_time": 294057.0,
      "text": "work best for certain types of materials."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 294057.0,
      "end_time": 297736.0,
      "text": "This is particularly true of the metallic and specular values"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 297736.0,
      "end_time": 301273.0,
      "text": "depending up which approach is being used"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 301273.0,
      "end_time": 303723.0,
      "text": "Taking specular colour for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 303723.0,
      "end_time": 306199.0,
      "text": "when analysing real-world materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 306199.0,
      "end_time": 308199.0,
      "text": "most materials have a specular range"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 308199.0,
      "end_time": 310768.0,
      "text": "that is a very dark grey."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 310768.0,
      "end_time": 315416.0,
      "text": "Metals created with a specular workflow are one of the few exceptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 315416.0,
      "end_time": 319043.0,
      "text": "they have very bright specular values."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 319043.0,
      "end_time": 322066.0,
      "text": "As well, no material, even the most dull,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 322066.0,
      "end_time": 324997.0,
      "text": "has no specularity at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 324997.0,
      "end_time": 326997.0,
      "text": "This means to have a physically based"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 326997.0,
      "end_time": 328997.0,
      "text": "material behave correctly"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 328997.0,
      "end_time": 330997.0,
      "text": "some attention needs to be paid in using"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 330997.0,
      "end_time": 334316.0,
      "text": "the correct physical values for some key properties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 334316.0,
      "end_time": 337149.0,
      "text": "especially the specular or metallic properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 337149.0,
      "end_time": 340224.0,
      "text": "depending upon the approach being used."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 340224.0,
      "end_time": 342863.0,
      "text": "For more information on physical-based shading,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 342863.0,
      "end_time": 345553.0,
      "text": "material charts and sample materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 345553.0,
      "end_time": 348512.0,
      "text": "please see the information linked below."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 348512.0,
      "end_time": 350512.0,
      "text": "There is no need to panic however."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 350512.0,
      "end_time": 353002.0,
      "text": "Items with materials from previous versions of Unity"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 353002.0,
      "end_time": 355894.0,
      "text": "will work well out of the box."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 355894.0,
      "end_time": 358214.0,
      "text": "Upgrading from a legacy diffuse shader"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 358214.0,
      "end_time": 363307.0,
      "text": "to the standard shader should display little or no difference."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 363307.0,
      "end_time": 365738.0,
      "text": "In the main map section each of these properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 365738.0,
      "end_time": 369127.0,
      "text": "control one aspect of the final material."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 369127.0,
      "end_time": 373328.0,
      "text": "Each property can be defined by a texture map."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 373328.0,
      "end_time": 375096.0,
      "text": "With the metallic approach,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 375096.0,
      "end_time": 378163.0,
      "text": "for the albido, metallic and emission properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 378163.0,
      "end_time": 380661.0,
      "text": "the texture is optional."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 380661.0,
      "end_time": 382904.0,
      "text": "The albido and emission properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 382904.0,
      "end_time": 386508.0,
      "text": "can simply use a colour value instead of a texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 386508.0,
      "end_time": 388416.0,
      "text": "The colour value is not available on"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 388416.0,
      "end_time": 390416.0,
      "text": "the emission property until the emissive"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 390416.0,
      "end_time": 394775.0,
      "text": "scale is larger than 0."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 394775.0,
      "end_time": 396775.0,
      "text": "The metallic property can use a slider"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 396775.0,
      "end_time": 402516.0,
      "text": "instead of a texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 402516.0,
      "end_time": 404516.0,
      "text": "The albido property uses a"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 404516.0,
      "end_time": 408543.0,
      "text": "combination of an optional texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 408543.0,
      "end_time": 412685.0,
      "text": "And a colour value to define the base look of the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 412685.0,
      "end_time": 417470.0,
      "text": "The colour value will tint the texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 417470.0,
      "end_time": 421552.0,
      "text": "Where pure white leaves the main texture unaffected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 421552.0,
      "end_time": 423552.0,
      "text": "if there is no texture being used"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 423552.0,
      "end_time": 429884.0,
      "text": "the tint colour will be the base colour for the material"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 429884.0,
      "end_time": 431884.0,
      "text": "The metallic property can be defined"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 431884.0,
      "end_time": 435248.0,
      "text": "by either a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 435248.0,
      "end_time": 438303.0,
      "text": "or a value from 0 to 1"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 438303.0,
      "end_time": 440303.0,
      "text": "set by the slider."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 440303.0,
      "end_time": 444538.0,
      "text": "This defines the metalness of the material surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 444538.0,
      "end_time": 448548.0,
      "text": "Metalness works very closely with smoothness."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 448548.0,
      "end_time": 450548.0,
      "text": "The smoothness property is used to"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 450548.0,
      "end_time": 452061.0,
      "text": "control the smoothness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 452061.0,
      "end_time": 455453.0,
      "text": "or micro-surface detail, of the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 455453.0,
      "end_time": 461028.0,
      "text": "It is also a value between 0 and 1."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 461028.0,
      "end_time": 463028.0,
      "text": "The less smooth the surface is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 463028.0,
      "end_time": 465360.0,
      "text": "the more diffuse the reflections will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 465360.0,
      "end_time": 472650.0,
      "text": "The more smooth, the sharper the reflections."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 472650.0,
      "end_time": 474650.0,
      "text": "The metallic property can use a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 474650.0,
      "end_time": 478071.0,
      "text": "to define the material&#39;s metalness."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 478071.0,
      "end_time": 480071.0,
      "text": "This texture can be a simple shade of grey"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 480071.0,
      "end_time": 483163.0,
      "text": "used to define the metalness from black,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 483163.0,
      "end_time": 484517.0,
      "text": "or non-metallic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 484517.0,
      "end_time": 487217.0,
      "text": "to white, completely metallic."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 487217.0,
      "end_time": 490339.0,
      "text": "However, the advantage of using a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 490339.0,
      "end_time": 492686.0,
      "text": "to define the metalness of a material"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 492686.0,
      "end_time": 494686.0,
      "text": "is to vary the metalness value"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 494686.0,
      "end_time": 497589.0,
      "text": "across the surface of the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 497589.0,
      "end_time": 501524.0,
      "text": "An additional advantage is this texture&#39;s alpha channel."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 501524.0,
      "end_time": 503524.0,
      "text": "This alpha channel can be used to define"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 503524.0,
      "end_time": 507791.0,
      "text": "a smoothness map."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 507791.0,
      "end_time": 509791.0,
      "text": "Many materials are far more complex"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 509791.0,
      "end_time": 512657.0,
      "text": "than a single uniform surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 512657.00000000006,
      "end_time": 515486.00000000006,
      "text": "Take this leather case for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 515486.0,
      "end_time": 517486.0,
      "text": "With a single value for metalness and a"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 517486.0,
      "end_time": 519615.0,
      "text": "single value for smoothness"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 519615.0,
      "end_time": 521615.0,
      "text": "the case looks good."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 521615.0,
      "end_time": 523891.0,
      "text": "But it could look better."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 523890.99999999994,
      "end_time": 525891.0,
      "text": "Use a metalness and smoothness map"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 525891.0,
      "end_time": 529660.0,
      "text": "to describe the properties."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 529660.0,
      "end_time": 531660.0,
      "text": "And it looks much better."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 531660.0,
      "end_time": 533660.0,
      "text": "Note how the straps are far more glossy"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 533660.0,
      "end_time": 535660.0,
      "text": "than the main body of the case."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 535660.0,
      "end_time": 538969.0,
      "text": "Giving them a feel of polished leather."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 538969.0,
      "end_time": 540969.0,
      "text": "It is worth noting that when using a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 540969.0,
      "end_time": 542969.0,
      "text": "to define the metalness"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 542969.0,
      "end_time": 544969.0,
      "text": "the smoothness value must also be"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 544969.0,
      "end_time": 547983.0,
      "text": "defined by that texture&#39;s alpha channel."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 547983.0,
      "end_time": 549983.0,
      "text": "It is also worth noting that the metalness"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 549983.0,
      "end_time": 551983.0,
      "text": "value is stored only in the red"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 551983.0,
      "end_time": 555990.0,
      "text": "channel of the metalness map&#39;s RGB values."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 555990.0,
      "end_time": 559059.0,
      "text": "The green and blue channels are ignored."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 559059.0,
      "end_time": 561923.0,
      "text": "It is often easier however to visualise"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 561923.0,
      "end_time": 563923.0,
      "text": "the metalness values of a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 563923.0,
      "end_time": 566709.0,
      "text": "if all three colour channels share the same map,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 566709.0,
      "end_time": 570716.0,
      "text": "so the texture appears as a greyscale image."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 570716.0,
      "end_time": 575615.0,
      "text": "When using the standard shader with the specular setup"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 575615.0,
      "end_time": 577615.0,
      "text": "the metallic property is replaced with"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 577615.0,
      "end_time": 579891.0,
      "text": "the specular property."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 579891.0,
      "end_time": 581891.0,
      "text": "The specular approach also uses"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 581891.0,
      "end_time": 584775.0,
      "text": "a smoothness property, which behaves essentially"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 584775.0,
      "end_time": 590956.0,
      "text": "in the same way as with the metalness approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 590956.0,
      "end_time": 595278.0,
      "text": "The specualar property can either be a texture"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 595278.0,
      "end_time": 597499.0,
      "text": "or a colour value"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 597499.0,
      "end_time": 599499.0,
      "text": "and defines the specular reflectivity"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 599499.0,
      "end_time": 601628.0,
      "text": "of the material&#39;s surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 601628.0,
      "end_time": 604527.0,
      "text": "The specular value can have some colour in it"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 604527.0,
      "end_time": 606527.0,
      "text": "but looking at real world values"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 606527.0,
      "end_time": 608527.0,
      "text": "with the exception of some metals"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 608527.0,
      "end_time": 612610.0,
      "text": "this is usually a grey and often very dark."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 612610.0,
      "end_time": 617545.0,
      "text": "Specular maps are usually a dark grey as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 617545.0,
      "end_time": 620332.0,
      "text": "When a specular texture map is not being used"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 620332.0,
      "end_time": 622332.0,
      "text": "the overall surface smoothness can be"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 622332.0,
      "end_time": 626765.0,
      "text": "set with the slider."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 626765.0,
      "end_time": 628765.0,
      "text": "This is easier to see when the albido"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 628765.0,
      "end_time": 631502.0,
      "text": "texture is removed."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 631502.0,
      "end_time": 634737.0,
      "text": "The ball looks like polished porcelain."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 634737.0,
      "end_time": 638692.0,
      "text": "For a more true mirror, the specular from dark grey,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 638692.0,
      "end_time": 640692.0,
      "text": "which makes the ball look like porcelain"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 640692.0,
      "end_time": 643547.0,
      "text": "in to the range of metals and it will now"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 643547.0,
      "end_time": 646487.0,
      "text": "reflect the sky and surroundings."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 646487.0,
      "end_time": 650330.0,
      "text": "The smoother the surface, the more it is mirror-like."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 650330.0,
      "end_time": 653077.0,
      "text": "The rougher the surface the more diffuse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 653077.0,
      "end_time": 656588.0,
      "text": "or scattered the reflections are."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 656588.0,
      "end_time": 658938.0,
      "text": "The normal map property is an optional property"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 658938.0,
      "end_time": 662893.0,
      "text": "used to define the apparent bumpiness of the surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 662893.0,
      "end_time": 665649.0,
      "text": "When a normal map is applied"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 665649.0,
      "end_time": 667649.0,
      "text": "the strength of the normal map can be controlled"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 667649.0,
      "end_time": 671033.0,
      "text": "by adjusting the normal map value."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 671033.0,
      "end_time": 673033.0,
      "text": "As well as positive numbers, this value"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 673033.0,
      "end_time": 675420.0,
      "text": "can be a negative number"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 675420.0,
      "end_time": 678040.0,
      "text": "or 0."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 678040.0,
      "end_time": 680040.0,
      "text": "The height map property is an optional"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 680040.0,
      "end_time": 682040.0,
      "text": "property used to define the apparent"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 682040.0,
      "end_time": 684040.0,
      "text": "height of the surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 684040.0,
      "end_time": 686667.0,
      "text": "When a height map is applied"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 686667.0,
      "end_time": 688667.0,
      "text": "the strength of the height map can be controlled"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 688667.0,
      "end_time": 692842.0,
      "text": "by adjusting the height map value."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 692842.0,
      "end_time": 694842.0,
      "text": "The occlusion property uses a"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 694842.0,
      "end_time": 696842.0,
      "text": "texture map to define the amount of"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 696842.0,
      "end_time": 700799.0,
      "text": "ambient occlusion that is applied to the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 700799.0,
      "end_time": 702799.0,
      "text": "This is used to help darken"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 702799.0,
      "end_time": 706200.0,
      "text": "hidden or recessed areas on the texture."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 706200.0,
      "end_time": 708200.0,
      "text": "The ambient occlusion map also"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 708200.0,
      "end_time": 710200.0,
      "text": "prevents specular and reflections in"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 710200.0,
      "end_time": 712676.0,
      "text": "these occluded areas, given the material"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 712676.0,
      "end_time": 716058.0,
      "text": "a more realistic look."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 716058.0,
      "end_time": 718690.0,
      "text": "The emission property controls whether or not"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 718690.0,
      "end_time": 721630.0,
      "text": "the material&#39;s surface will emit light."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 721630.0,
      "end_time": 723630.0,
      "text": "The material&#39;s emission value can contribute"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 723630.0,
      "end_time": 726791.0,
      "text": "to the scene&#39;s global illumination."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 726791.0,
      "end_time": 728791.0,
      "text": "The strength of the emission can be controlled"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 728791.0,
      "end_time": 731215.0,
      "text": "by the emission value."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 731215.0,
      "end_time": 735359.0,
      "text": "The shape of the emission can be controlled with an emission map."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 735359.0,
      "end_time": 743699.0,
      "text": "The map can be a simple black and white map."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 743699.0,
      "end_time": 752529.0,
      "text": "bBut this texture can also be a colour map."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 752529.0,
      "end_time": 754529.0,
      "text": "When there is a value for emission"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 754529.0,
      "end_time": 756529.0,
      "text": "the contribution of the emissive light"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 756529.0,
      "end_time": 760607.0,
      "text": "can be assigned to either the baked light maps"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 760607.0,
      "end_time": 765740.0,
      "text": "or to the real time light maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 765740.0,
      "end_time": 768930.0,
      "text": "The detail mask property is an optional mask element"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 768930.0,
      "end_time": 772054.0,
      "text": "to control the secondary maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 772054.0,
      "end_time": 775961.0,
      "text": "Tiling and offset control the position of the map."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 775961.0,
      "end_time": 777961.0,
      "text": "The secondary maps are used to define"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 777961.0,
      "end_time": 779961.0,
      "text": "additional surface detail."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 779961.0,
      "end_time": 783608.0,
      "text": "This additional detail, sometimes referred to as micro detail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 783608.0,
      "end_time": 785608.0,
      "text": "is added on top of the surface defined"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 785608.0,
      "end_time": 787848.0,
      "text": "by the main maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 787848.0,
      "end_time": 789848.0,
      "text": "This helps to add extra detail and"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 789848.0,
      "end_time": 792657.0,
      "text": "variation to a material, which is overlaid"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 792657.0,
      "end_time": 796187.0,
      "text": "on top of the main maps defining that material."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 796187.0,
      "end_time": 799899.0,
      "text": "Because detail maps can be tiled across meshes"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 799899.0,
      "end_time": 809899.0,
      "text": "they can add incredibly high levels of surface detail."
    }
  ]
}